          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                                        <date>May 27 1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir. Long absence<lb/> from the city has
                                        prevented me from<lb/> writing you at an earlier period.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am glad to see that you are about<lb/> to
                                        continue the Occident &amp; sincerely hope<lb/> that you may
                                        meet with increased &amp;<lb/> liberal patronage. If you
                                        will draw off<lb/> a list of those who subscribe to it
                                        in<lb/> this place, &amp; send it to me, I will call on<lb/>
                                        many of those who <hi rend="underline">are not</hi>
                                        subscribers<lb/> &amp; may be enabled to extend the
                                        number<lb/> here. <persName>Charles F Levy</persName>,
                                                  <persName>Chas H Moise</persName><lb/> &amp;
                                        myself have read <hi rend="underline">the Occident</hi>
                                        when<lb/> we were put down for the <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >Advocate</hi>.<lb/> The former <sic>dont</sic>
                                        object &amp; says he will<lb/> take the Occident, but
                                                  <persName>Chas Moise</persName> says<lb/> his
                                        Father takes it &amp; one copy suffices<lb/> while for
                                        myself the copy mother receives<lb/> is enough, as we reside
                                        together.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am not aware of any others who have<lb/>
                                        received the Occident instead of the Advocate<lb/> but if
                                        there are more they may decline<lb/> payment. Yrs Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <persName role="author">Thos J Moise</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
